Remote system : GITHUB 
Local system : OUR PC 

1. To add a github repo to our system we use command : git clone <url>      (url of the repo from github)

2. To list all items : ls
3. to list hdden items : ls -a   or   ls -h

4. To change directory : cd <name of the directory>     

5. To check status : git status

6. To add changes done in a file : git add <file name>
7. To add all the changes done : git add .

8. To commit changes : git commit -m"<the message for commit>"

9. To push you code : git push origin main